  "wikitext": "\n'''2-3-215\n\nNo English Term\n\nA filament (usually of multi-vee formation) in the form of a hollow truncated cone, generated around the axis of the lamp.\n\n[[Image:Ch2_Fig30.jpg|400px|border]]\n\n\nNote: The filament may be fully closed in plan, or may embrace an arc of less than 360 degrees.\n\nIn the latter case, the French term is Grille Tronconique Incomplete or Filament Tronconique Incomplet and the English term is\"Bunch filament\" (2-3-220).\n\n\n{{IALAFooter}}\n\n{{languages|Hollow truncated cone filament}}\n[[Category:2.3 Light Sources]]\n[[Category:Alphabetical Index]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 1970-89 Edition]]"
